{"lemma":"حالٌ","slug":"حالٌ","root":"ح.#.ل","root_slug":"ح-_-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-_-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حالٌ","root":"حول","pos":"V","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","prep","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":15},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8758","n8982","n9572","n9780","n9581"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to change, to be transformed"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to turn, to transform"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dodge, to evade"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to elapse, to pass, to go by"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to intervene, to come","examples":[{"text":"وَٱعْلَمُوا أَنَّ اللّٰهَ يَحُولُ بَيْنَ المَرْءِ وَقَلْبِهِ","english":"And know that God stands between a person and their heart […]"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to prevent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"condition, state, situation, position, status, circumstance, matter, concern, being"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"current circumstances, present, actuality"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"present","tags":["present"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a circumstantial expression, adverbial"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"during, right after, immediately upon"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of حَلَى (ḥalā)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"wearing an ornament or jewellery"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"having an ornament or jewellery"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Adverbial accusative of حَال (ḥāl, “circumstance”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8758","headword_ar":"حَالٌّ","root":"Hl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Untying, undoing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opening,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a knot:]"},{"kind":"page_break","n":622},{"kind":"text","text":"act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a","text_ar":"حَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a AlEuqodapa","text_ar":"حَلَّ العُقْدَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  [And hence, (see 1,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Alighting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"descending and stopping"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sojourning"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abiding"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lodging"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"settling;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking up one's abode;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abiding, lodging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"settling;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a place; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAzilN","text_ar":"نَازِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~N","text_ar":"حِلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; occurring in the Kur xc. 2: (TA:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuluwlN","text_ar":"حُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hul~aAlN","text_ar":"حُلَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hul~alN","text_ar":"حُلَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and quasi-pl. n. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~apN","text_ar":"حِلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA [in which it is in one place called a pl. (not a quasi-pl. n.) of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAl~N","text_ar":"حَالٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"];) and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~apN","text_ar":"حِلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilaAlN","text_ar":"حِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~N HuluwlN","text_ar":"حَىٌّ حُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tribe that is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abiding"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in one place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 171.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN Hil~apN","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ حِلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, alighting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., (S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and comprising a numerous company:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiY~N Hil~apN","text_ar":"حِىٌّ حِلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~N HilaAlN","text_ar":"حَىٌّ حِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a numerous tribe"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alighting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naZarN","text_ar":"نَظَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaAl~u AlmurotaHilu","text_ar":"الحَالُّ المُرْتَحِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who completes the reading,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reciting, of the Kur-án, and then immediately recommences it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"likened to him who travels much, and does not come to his family: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the warrior who does not return from his warring."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayonN HaAlN","text_ar":"دَيْنٌ حَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A debt of which the appointed term,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period, is ended;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a debt falling due;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^aj~alN","text_ar":"مُوَجَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHal~alN","text_ar":"مُحَلَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["TA","K","S","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n8982","headword_ar":"حَالٍ","root":"HlY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAliyapN","text_ar":"حَالِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) A woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having an ornament or ornaments;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haliy~apN","text_ar":"حَلِيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wearing an ornament"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ornaments;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaHal~iyapN","text_ar":"مُتَحَلِّيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAlK","text_ar":"حَوَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  And [hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAliyapN","text_ar":"حَالِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)  Trees"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having leaves and fruit."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S"]},{"entry_id":"n9572","headword_ar":"حَالَ","root":"Hwl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHuwlu","text_ar":"يَحُولُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Msb, Er-Rághib,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawolN","text_ar":"حَوْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huw^uwlN","text_ar":"حُوُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, Er-Rághib) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawalaAnN","text_ar":"حَوَلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became altered, transmuted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"changed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Mgh, Msb, Er-Rághib, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from its state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from its natural state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its constitution;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstHAl","text_ar":"استحال","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHw~l","text_ar":"تحوّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K:) which [here] signifies [as above; or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became altered, transmuted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"changed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"essentially"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"substantially,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of predicament"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by saying;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHAl","text_ar":"احال","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (K:) or this last is said of a man meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino $aYo'K A_ilaY $aYo'K","text_ar":"مِنْ شَىْءٍ اـِلَى شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHw~l","text_ar":"تحوّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he shifted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turned, from one thing to another"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) and hence, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became a Muslim:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K, TA:) for in this case one says of a man,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~aA kaAna","text_ar":"عَمَّا كَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHw~l","text_ar":"تحوّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEobudu A_ilaY AlA_isolaAmi","text_ar":"يَعْبُدُ اـِلَى الاـِسْلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he turned from that which he was worshipping to El-Islám"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAar, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl","text_ar":"حال"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAlN","text_ar":"مَحَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiylapN","text_ar":"حِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtAl","text_ar":"احتال"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (Ham p. 652.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl","text_ar":"حال"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstHAl","text_ar":"استحال","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(anything)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shifted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became shifted"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"transferred;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHw~l","text_ar":"تحوّل"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it moved;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHr~k","text_ar":"تحرّك"},{"kind":"text","text":": so accord. to different copies of the K: or, accord. to the O, the former verb has both of these significations: (TA:) or it has the latter of these significations, said of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axoS","text_ar":"شَخْص"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. a man, or person, or the figure of a thing seen from a distance]: (S:) or both verbs signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(anything)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became altered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"changed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from straightness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evenness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to crookedness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unevenness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlati Alqawosu","text_ar":"حَالَتِ القَوْسُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bow became crooked"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the portion between the part grasped by the hand and the curved extremity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the curved extremity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reverted from the state into which it was brought by pressure"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viqaAf","text_ar":"ثِقَاف"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and became crooked in the portion between the part grasped by the hand and the curved extremity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstHAlt","text_ar":"استحالت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDu Eani AlAisotiwaA='i A_ilaY","text_ar":"الاَرْضُ عَنِ الاِسْتِوَا=ءِ اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstHAlti","text_ar":"استحالتِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEiwaji","text_ar":"العِوَجِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ground became altered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"changed, from evenness to unevenness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or [simply] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstHAlt","text_ar":"استحالت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became uneven:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlArD","text_ar":"الارض"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaAlati","text_ar":"اَحَالَتِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Smt","text_ar":"صمت"},{"kind":"text","text":") app. signifies the same:] or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstHAl","text_ar":"استحال","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was disposed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was about, to become altered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"changed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl lawonuhu","text_ar":"حال لَوْنُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Its colour altered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"changed, and became black."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl","text_ar":"حال"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shifted from its way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direction."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl wataru","text_ar":"حال وَتَرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawosi","text_ar":"القَوْسِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The string of the bow shifted from its place"},{"kind":"text","text":"on the occasion of shooting: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlati Alqawosu","text_ar":"حَالَتِ القَوْسُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watarahaA","text_ar":"وَتَرَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the bow shifted from its string."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl mino makaAnihi","text_ar":"حال مِنْ مَكَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiwalN","text_ar":"حِوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, TA,) or this is a simple subst., (S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, shifted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removed, from his,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its, place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiwalN","text_ar":"حِوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl A_ilaY makaAnK A=xiri","text_ar":"حال اـِلَى مَكَانٍ ا=خِرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHw~l","text_ar":"تحوّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, shifted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became shifted"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"transferred, to another place"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl Eani AlEahodi","text_ar":"حال عَنِ العَهْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huw^uwlN","text_ar":"حُوُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anqlb","text_ar":"انقلب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He withdrew,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"receded, from the covenant, compact, agreement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"engagement"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl fiY matoni farasihi","text_ar":"حال فِى مَتْنِ فَرَسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huw^uwlN","text_ar":"حُوُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He leaped, and rode, upon the back of his horse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHAl","text_ar":"احال","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl fiY Zahori daAb~atihi","text_ar":"حال فِى ظَهْرِ دَابَّتِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he leaped, and seated himself firmly, upon the back of his beast;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHAl","text_ar":"احال","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl EalaY","text_ar":"حال عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfarasi","text_ar":"الفَرَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawolapN","text_ar":"حَوْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he seated himself firmly upon the horse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl SabuwHuhumo EalaY gabuwqihimo","text_ar":"حال صَبُوحُهُمْ عَلَى غَبُوقِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Their morning-draught and their evening-draught became one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said of people suffering from drought, and scarcity of milk. (TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl","text_ar":"حال"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, K,) aor. as above, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawolN","text_ar":"حَوْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) said of a year ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawolN","text_ar":"حَوْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It passed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it revolved and passed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became complete."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl Ealayohi AlHawolu","text_ar":"حال عَلَيْهِ الحَوْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawolN","text_ar":"حَوْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huw^uwlN","text_ar":"حُوُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The year passed over him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, became a year old;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHAl","text_ar":"احال","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl","text_ar":"حال"},{"kind":"text","text":", alone, (Msb, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHAl","text_ar":"احال","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHowala","text_ar":"اَحْوَلَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The year passed over it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHAl","text_ar":"احال","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHowala","text_ar":"اَحْوَلَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtAl","text_ar":"احتال","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A year passed over it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became a year old;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K, TA;) said of wheat, or food, and of other things: (S, TA:) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAlt","text_ar":"حالت"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHAlt","text_ar":"احالت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHowalato","text_ar":"اَحْوَلَتْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dAr","text_ar":"دار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or house]: (S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlati Ald~aAru","text_ar":"حَالَتِ الدَّارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHAlt","text_ar":"احالت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHowalat","text_ar":"اَحْوَلَت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hiyla biAld~aAri","text_ar":"حِيلَ بِالدَّارِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"years passed over the house:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the house became altered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"changed, and years passed over it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaAmat","text_ar":"اَعَامَت"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oharat","text_ar":"اَشْهَرَت"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl","text_ar":"حال"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a boy,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A year passed over him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became a year old;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHwl","text_ar":"احول","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlmakaAni","text_ar":"بِالمَكَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHAl","text_ar":"احال","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHowala","text_ar":"اَحْوَلَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He remained, stayed, abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dwelt, a year in the place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, S, Msb, K:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlato","text_ar":"حَالَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiyaAlN","text_ar":"حِيَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiyaAlapN","text_ar":"حِيَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huw^uwlN","text_ar":"حُوُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuwlN","text_ar":"حُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHAlt","text_ar":"احالت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hw~lt","text_ar":"حوّلت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) said of a she-camel, (S, K,) &c., (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She did not conceive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become pregnant, during a year,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two years,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"some years:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she, having been covered by the stallion, did not become pregnant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or, said of a woman, and of a she-camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she did not become pregnant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAlt","text_ar":"حالت"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHAlt","text_ar":"احالت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) said of a palm-tree ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naxolapN","text_ar":"نَخْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It bore one year, and not another year:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did not bear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having been fecundated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl Al$~aYo'u bayoniY wabayonaka","text_ar":"حال الشَّىْءُ بَيْنِى وَبَيْنَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Er-Rághib,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona","text_ar":"بَيْنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ayoy^ayoni","text_ar":"الشَّيْيَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, * K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayoluwlapN","text_ar":"حَيْلُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayowaluwlapN","text_ar":"حَيْوَلُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (Mgh, Msb,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayonuwnapN","text_ar":"كَيْنُونَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.], (Mgh,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huw^uwlN","text_ar":"حُوُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawolN","text_ar":"حَوْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Er-Rághib, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thing intervened as a separation, a partition, a fence, a barrier,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an obstacle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obstruction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, Er-Rághib, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between me and thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Er-Rághib, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the two things."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl Aln~ahoru bayonanaA","text_ar":"حال النَّهْرُ بَيْنَنَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The river intervened as a separation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an obstacle, between us, preventing conjunction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"communication."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl Al$~aYo'u duwna Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"حال الشَّىْءُ دُونَ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thing intervened as an obstacle in the way to the thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotaraDa","text_ar":"اِعْتَرَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) It is said in the Kur [viii. 24],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@EolamuwA","text_ar":"وَا@عْلَمُوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^an~a A@ll~`ha yaHuwlu bayona Almaro'i waqalobihi","text_ar":"اَنَّ ا@للّٰهَ يَحُولُ بَيْنَ المَرْءِ وَقَلْبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And know ye that God interveneth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interposeth, between the man and his heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"secret thoughts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desire"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: indicating that He turns him from his desire: (Er-Rághib, TA:) or that He possesses his heart, and"},{"kind":"page_break","n":674},{"kind":"text","text":"turns it as He wills: (O, TA:) or that a man cannot believe nor disbelieve unless it be God's will: (Jel:) or, as some say, that God destroys a man; or reduces him to the vilest condition of life, in order that he may not know, after knowing, anything. (Er-Rághib, TA. [See other remote interpretations in the Ksh, and the Expos. of Bd.]) And in the same [xxxiv. 53],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHiyla bayonahumo wa bayona","text_ar":"وَحِيلَ بَيْنَهُمْ وَ بَيْنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA ya$otahuwna","text_ar":"مَا يَشْتَهُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And an obstacle shall be made to intervene between them and that which they shall eagerly desire"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b9-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl Al$~aYo'u","text_ar":"حال الشَّىْءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thing poured out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also 4.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hawilato Eayonuhu","text_ar":"حَوِلَتْ عَيْنُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlato","text_ar":"حَالَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHaAlu","text_ar":"تَحَالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) the latter, of the dial. of Temeem, accord. to Lth, (TA,) [but see what follows,] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawalN","text_ar":"حَوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Mgh, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHwl~t","text_ar":"احولّت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiHowilaAlN","text_ar":"اِحْوِلَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His eye"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"squinted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had the white apparent at the outer angle, and the black next the inner angle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had the black turning towards the nose:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had one of the two blacks turned towards the nose, and the other towards the temple:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had its black next the outer angle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his eye was as though it looked towards the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HijaAj","text_ar":"حِجَاج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supraorbital bone"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had the black inclining towards the outer angle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) the first of which meanings is that commonly known: but some say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlato","text_ar":"حَالَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies it was turned from its proper state: or it is anomalous: (TA:) the epithet applied to the man is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHowalu","text_ar":"اَحْوَلُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawilN","text_ar":"حَوِلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and that applied to the eye is [the fem. of the former of these, i. e.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawolaA='u","text_ar":"حَوْلَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) the pl. of which, and of the masc., is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuwlN","text_ar":"حُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Har p. 412.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","K","TA","IAar","M","O","Msb","Ks","Jel","Lth"]},{"entry_id":"n9780","headword_ar":"حَالَ","root":"Hyl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHiylu","text_ar":"يَحِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuyuwlN","text_ar":"حُيُولٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It became altered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"changed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl","text_ar":"حال"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHuwlu","text_ar":"يَحُولُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huw^uwlN","text_ar":"حُوُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl AlmaA='u","text_ar":"حال المَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The water remained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stagnated, and collected;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remained long, and became altered;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became yellow and altered;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the bottom of a valley. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n9581","headword_ar":"حَالٌ","root":"Hwl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state, condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sifap","text_ar":"صِفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of a thing; [considered as subject to change;] (Msb, Er-Rághib, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlapN","text_ar":"حَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner of being,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man, (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of good or evil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlapN","text_ar":"حَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"particular case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"predicament,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man &c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of changing events, in the soul and the body and the acquisitions:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA:) and in the coventional language of the logicians,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fleeting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly-transient, quality, such as accidental heat and cold and moisture and dryness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlapN","text_ar":"حَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything changing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 288:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time in which one is;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K;) [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"present time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"end of the past,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beginning of the future:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and as a conventional term, [in grammar, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"present tense:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"future:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a denotative of state"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the agent or of the objective complement; [the former termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlN mina AlfaAEili","text_ar":"حَالٌ مِنَ الفَاعِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the latter,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlN mina AlmafoEuwli","text_ar":"حَالٌ مِنَ المَفْعُولِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and each said to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manoSuwbN","text_ar":"مَنْصُوبٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY AlHaAli","text_ar":"عَلَى الحَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put in the accus. case as a denotative of state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"unless expressed by a complete proposition;] as ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAy^imFA","text_ar":"قَايِمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodN fiY","text_ar":"زَيْدٌ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAra qaAy^imFA","text_ar":"الدَّارَ قَايِمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[Zeyd is in the house, standing], and in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Darabotu zayodFA qaAy^imFA","text_ar":"ضَرَبْتُ زَيْدًا قَايِمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[I beat Zeyd standing]: (Ibn-El-Kemál, TA:) it is fem., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlapN","text_ar":"حَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and mase. ; (Msb, K;) but mostly fem.: (TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHowaAlN","text_ar":"اَحْوَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHowilapN","text_ar":"اَحْوِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [both properly pls. of pauc., but the former often used as a pl. of mult., and often signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the latter anomalous: (TA:) the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlapN","text_ar":"حَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlaAtN","text_ar":"حَالَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAlp","text_ar":"حالة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un. or sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlN","text_ar":"حَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHowaAlN","text_ar":"اَحْوَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlaAtN","text_ar":"حَالَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], used in relation to a man. (S, O.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlN HasanN","text_ar":"حَالٌ حَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanapN","text_ar":"حَسَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A good state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlapN","text_ar":"حَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanapN","text_ar":"حَسَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahori","text_ar":"الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlaAtu","text_ar":"حَالَاتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHowaAluhu","text_ar":"اَحْوَالُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The changes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vicissitudes, of time"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fortune."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifoEalohu HaAlFA","text_ar":"اِفْعَلْهُ حَالًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlHaAli","text_ar":"فِى الحَالِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Do thou it now,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"immediately."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY kul~i HaAlK","text_ar":"عَلَى كُلِّ حَالٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In any case:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a phrase of frequent occurrence. The phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAla lisaAnu AlHaAli","text_ar":"قَالَ لِسَانُ الحَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tongue of the case said,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(often used by late writers,) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the case seemed to say."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A load,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burden:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 299:) [whence, perhaps,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafiyfu AlHaAli","text_ar":"خَفِيفُ الحَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which see in what follows) as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a small family to maintain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and hence, (Ham ib.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bundle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bundle of clothes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaArapN","text_ar":"كَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is carried on the back"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Ham ib.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by a man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that a man carries on his back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whatever it be."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which one collects,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeks and collects, dry herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of stuff, of which two ends are tied in a knot behind the flanks, and the other two ends over the head; in which one collects dry herbage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ukobaAnN","text_ar":"شُكْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$kb","text_ar":"شكب"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A child's go-cart, by means of which he practises walking;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K *, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling a small"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajalap","text_ar":"عَجَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dar~aAjapN","text_ar":"دَرَّاجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S, TA.)       -A4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libod","text_ar":"لِبْد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saddle-cloth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"line along the middle of the back:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlu matoni Alfarasi","text_ar":"حَالُ مَتْنِ الفَرَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the middle of the back of the horse; the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libodi","text_ar":"لِبْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) [See also its syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaA*N","text_ar":"حَاذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafiyfu AlHaAli","text_ar":"خَفِيفُ الحَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafiyfu AlHaA*i","text_ar":"خَفِيفُ الحَاذِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hw*","text_ar":"حوذ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) which means (tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light of back;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, Msb, all in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hw*","text_ar":"حوذ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having little property:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a small family to maintain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L in that art. ;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having little property and a small family to maintain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L and K in that art. ;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafiyfu AlZ~ahori","text_ar":"خَفِيفُ الظَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, L, Msb, all in that art.)       -A5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Black mud:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAla","text_ar":"حَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ it became altered, or changed. ” (TA.) It is said in a trad. that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl","text_ar":"حال"},{"kind":"text","text":"of El-Kowthar is musk: (TA:) and in another, that Gabriel took of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl","text_ar":"حال"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the river [Nile] and put it into the mouth of Pharaoh; (S, TA;) but here it has the meaning next following. (TA.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Black fetid mud;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoA^apN","text_ar":"حَمْاَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, and Ham p. 288.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Soft earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, and Ham ib.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weakness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"softness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham ib.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stinking flesh-meat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham ib.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hot ashes"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K, and Ham ib.) ―         -b5-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaves of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samur","text_ar":"سَمُر"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acacia,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mimosa, gummifera,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beaten and shaken off into a garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)       -A6-  In the dial. of Hudheyl, (IAar, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wife."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","TA","S","ISd","O","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}